The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 15 October is 82,490 (9,507.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 October, there were 2,634 new confirmed cases (303.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 October, there were 2,462 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 7% (172 extra cases).
